  "commentary": "With SPX at 6594.46 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6590 (-15.2B) and positive gamma resistance at 6605 (+16.3B), dealers are caught in a violent hedging zone where they're forced to buy any dip toward 6590 and sell any push above 6600. The breakout regime with -18.6B total GEX means dealers are amplifying moves in both directions, creating a explosive setup where a break below 6590 triggers accelerated selling while a sustained move above 6605 faces heavy dealer selling pressure. Watch 6590 as the critical amplifying level - a breakdown here likely cascades through the 6585/6580 negative gamma cluster, while 6605 acts as the key resistance where dealer selling intensifies.\n\nBottom line: expect violent swings between 6590-6605 with big moves likely if either level breaks.",
